title: Carl Dolan Memorial Spring Classic
description: 20TH Annual Carl Dolan Memorial Spring Classic
course: A 2.1 mile loop with a short climb at the Gateway Business Park, Columbia, MD.
registration: Online registration through bikereg.com. Day of registration available for non closed fields for an additional fee
directions: From I95 between Baltimore and Washington, take route 175 W/ exit #41w towards  Columbia. Take the exit to Columbia Gateway Dr. Follow to race course.

title: Bike Line Spring XC @ Fair Hill
description: Bike Line\'s Spring XC @ Fair Hill is one of the premier races of the Mid Atlantic Super Series.
course: Each lap is approximately 7.5 miles of ripping Fair Hill trails consisting of 75% singletrack. The course contains a number of fast flat to slightly rolling sections with most climbing being relatively short in duration. Most of the double track will be in the beginning and end of each lap, making for an exciting sprint finish. This is a great way for racers to start their XC season.
registration:
On-line registration available on BikeReg 
www.bikereg.com
Day of registration will be available
directions: North Appleton Road parking area in the Fair Hill Natural Resources Management Area. The parking area is located at the intersection of Black Bridge and Appleton Rd.(MD Rt. 316) Driving directions and map can be found on a mapping service or GPS using the following address: 2900 Appleton Rd. Elkton, MD. 21921

title: Mountain Massacree
description:
Mountain Massacree road race held in Garrett County in the hills of western Maryland.

Organized by the same company that produces the internationally renowned SavageMan Triathlon and Garrett County Gran Fondo, the Mountain Massacree is a 37 and 55 mile road race that is certain to become a Mid-Atlantic classic.
course:
Experience all the fun of the spring classics with none of the airfare.

Steep, punchy Appalachian climbs.  Long, fast descents.  Rural mountain roads lined with livestock and sprinkled with the occasional flavor of Belgian toothpaste.  1.5 mile, steep dirt road finish climb.

A road race course designed after the terrain, small roads, and tough climbs of the Belgian spring classics.
notes: Mountain Massacree benefits the Joanna M Nicolay Melanoma Foundation
directions:
Registration and packet pickup held at Accident Elementary School in Accident, Md.  Short, mass field rolldown to start line from there.

http://goo.gl/maps/RS56o

title: Highway To Heaven Hill Climb Time Trial
Schaeffer Farm Speedster
description:
Schaeffer Farm Speedster
A fun fast Cross Country mountain bike race on some of the best trails in the region.
course:
The Course
The course consists of about 9.7 miles of fast flowing single track with a few short steep climbs.
registration:
Pre-Register at BikeReg.com https://www.bikereg.com/Net/19291

Onsite registration is available for an extra $10 fee.  We take Visa/MC/AMEX for registration.
notes:
Fun Stuff to Do Near the Race
South Germantown Rec Park is amazing.  It has multiple playgrounds, indoor and outdoor splash parks, tennis courts, and a driving range.  Bring the family and make a full day of it...  Full description of the park.
directions:
IMPORTANT!  Parking is NOT at Schaeffer Farm MTB Park.  Parking is across Schaeffer Road in the large parking lot for Soccer Fields 18-22 at the South Germantown Recreation Park (Park Map).  

Take 270 to Exit 15B (South on MD118/Germantown Rd).  Take this about 3.7 miles to Germantown Park Dr, which is the marked as the entrance to South Germantown Rec Park.  It is a right turn only.  Follow Germantown Park Dr to the traffic Circle, go strait through the circle.  Take the first left past the circle, the parking lot for fields 18-22 will be on your left.  Follow the signs to the Registration which will be in the small parking lot next to Schaeffer Farm MTB Park.
